record_data.record_title: The Narragansett Electric Company FERC Electric Tariff No. 2
record_data.record_plain_text: THE NARRAGANSETT ELECTRIC COMPANY Market-Based Sales Tariff 1. Availability. Under this Tariff, The Narragansett Electric Company ("Narragansett") shall make available from time to time: (a) electric energy and/or capacity for sale at Narragansett's sole discretion; (b) the following ancillary services: (1) New York: Narragansett offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc. (2) New England: Narragansett offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc. (c) third-party ancillary services: Narragansett offers Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, Operating Reserve Supplemental, and Primary Frequency Response Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider's OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization. 2. Applicability. This Tariff is applicable to all FERC-jurisdictional sales of electric energy or capacity by Narragansett not otherwise subject to a particular Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ("FERC" or the "Commission") rate schedule or tariff of Narragansett. 3. Rates. All sales under this Tariff shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Narragansett or established pursuant to market rules or tariff provisions accepted by the FERC. 4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of sale shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Narragansett. 5. Effective Date. This Tariff is effective on the date authorized by FERC. 6. Changes in Rates, Terms and Conditions. Nothing herein affects the right of Narragansett to unilaterally make application to the FERC for a change of rates, terms or conditions of this Tariff pursuant to Section 205 of the Federal Power Act and regulations thereunder. 7. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Narragansett shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Narragansett's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Narragansett to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Narragansett's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Narragansett's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff. 8. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. Seller lacks market-based rate authority in the Louisville Gas and Electric Company/Kentucky Utilities balancing authority area. LG&E Energy Marketing Inc., Docket Nos. ER06-1046-000, et al., Letter Order, July 6, 2006, as clarified by Louisville Gas & Electric Co., et al., 135 FERC ? 61,281 (2011). 9. Seller Category. Narragansett is a Category 2 seller in the Northeast region, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a). Narragansett is a Category 1 seller in the Central, Northwest, Southeast, Southwest, and Southwest Power Pool regions, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a).
